NEWS_API_KEY# ============================================
# 🔐 Environment Variables (Example Template)
# ============================================
#
# This file provides a template for required environment variables.
# It should be copied and renamed to `.env` for local development.
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT:
# - Never commit your real `.env` file to version control
# - This file is safe to commit because it contains no secrets
#
# --------------------------------------------
# 📡 NEWS_API_KEY
# --------------------------------------------
# API key used to authenticate requests to the News API
# (https://newsapi.org/)
#
# Usage:
# - Required by `fetchArticles` service to retrieve news data
# - Imported in code via: import { NEWS_API_KEY } from '@env'
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Replace placeholder with your real API key:
#    NEWS_API_KEY=your_real_api_key_here
#
# 3. Restart the app:
#    npx react-native start --reset-cache
#
# Failure Scenarios:
# - Missing key → request will fail
# - Invalid key → API returns 401 (Unauthorized)
# - Rate limit → API returns 429 (Too Many Requests)
#
NEWS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here=your_api_key_here